T*
(- Executive Summary) Tj
T*
(Atho is a post-quantum UTXO blockchain that uses Falcon-512 signatures, SHA3-384 hashing, and a) Tj
T*
(120-second block target. The system is optimized around a hybrid architecture:) Tj
T*
(- Python for orchestration, APIs, and operator control.) Tj
T*
(- Native C/C++ binaries for cryptographic and performance-critical loops.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current direction is throughput and determinism:) Tj
T*
(- compact binary transaction wire format,) Tj
T*
(- integer atom accounting end-to-end,) Tj
T*
(- hash-pinned native binary loading,) Tj
T*
(- CPU/GPU miner backends under one consensus path.) Tj
T*
(- Bonded Proof of Work \(BPoW\) with wallet staking as a separate role.) Tj
T*
(- Current Protocol Direction) Tj
T*
(Compared with earlier snapshots, the current implementation formalizes these changes:) Tj
T*
(- Binary-first transaction transport:) Tj
T*
(- Canonical transport codec is compact binary \(ATX2, with ATX1 decode compatibility\).) Tj
T*
(- Witness is handled as raw bytes internally.) Tj
T*
(- Integer accounting standardization:) Tj
T*
(- Consensus-critical value math is integer atoms.) Tj
T*
(- Display formats remain user-facing \(ATHO, decimal strings, Base56 addresses\) without changing) Tj
T*
(internal math semantics.) Tj
T*
(- Native acceleration and binary governance:) Tj
T*
(- Native bridges for signing-body hashing, UTXO batch checks, and CPU mining loops.) Tj
T*
(- GPU miner binaries \(OpenCL baseline, CUDA where available\).) Tj
T*
(- Per-binary SHA3-384 pinning and metadata in Binaries/.) Tj
T*
(- Updated throughput model:) Tj
T*
(- Capacity estimates now use measured/derived vsize distributions rather than a fixed baseline) Tj
T*
(tx size.) Tj
T*
(- BPoW + wallet staking economics:) Tj
T*
(- miner eligibility is controlled by deterministic bond state,) Tj
T*
(- staking remains separate from block production,) Tj
T*
(- fee routing is deterministic and auditable at block level.) Tj
T*
(- Protocol Snapshot) Tj
T*
(- Block interval target: 120 seconds.) Tj
T*
(- Difficulty retarget interval: 180 blocks.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction confirmations required: 10.) Tj
T*
(- Coinbase maturity: 150 blocks.) Tj
T*
(- Block cap: 2,500,000 base bytes, 10,000,000 weight units.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction policy cap: 250,000 vB per transaction.) Tj
T*
(- Transaction policy metric: SegWit-style vsize.) Tj
T*
(- Addressing: Base56 for users, HPK-based internal destination binding.) Tj
T*
(- Signature system: Falcon-512.) Tj
T*
(- Hashing: SHA3-384 for canonical tx/block identity operations.) Tj
T*
(- Active fee floor: 225 atoms/vB.) Tj
T*
(- Active min tx fee: 150,000 atoms.) Tj
